# Line-ending policy.
#
# AID ships POSIX shell scripts that adopters run via bash, and run_generator.py
# always writes LF. Forcing LF for shell/JS/Python text prevents a contributor
# whose git core.autocrlf=true (this repo is authored on Windows) from committing
# CRLF that would break `#!/usr/bin/env bash` on Linux/macOS adopters — and would
# break the byte-exact render-drift CI gate.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.mjs  text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
# Markdown must be LF too: build-index.sh's awk frontmatter parser chokes on
# CRLF on Linux (intent: blocks parse as "no intent declared"), which broke the
# kb-hygiene CI check.
*.md   text eol=lf
